Adult.description: Mangrove Cuckoos have peachy washed underparts while Black-billed Cuckoos have white underparts. They also have a bicolored bill, but Black-billed Cuckoos have a solid black bill.
Yellow-billed Cuckoos have large white spots on the underside of the tail while Black-billed Cuckoos only have small white tips on the tail feathers. Note name implied bill color difference.
